# Serial recording started at: Sun Jun 08 12:30:00 2026
# Format: [timestamp_ms] direction byte|byte|byte|...
# Direction: R=read (from device), W=write (to device)
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Richer captured RS-485 session for end-to-end replay tests: an AquaRite
# salt-water generator (SWG, device id 0x50) that changes its generating level
# and salt concentration over the course of the session.  Unlike
# sample_session.cap (a single 40% / 3200 PPM snapshot) this fixture exercises
# the decode pipeline across STATE TRANSITIONS so the final decoded DataHub
# state reflects the LAST frame of each kind, proving the replay applies every
# frame in order rather than just the first.
#
# Timeline:
#   * GetId   (0x14) : Master -> SWG identification query.
#   * Percent (0x11) : generating level 40% -> then 60% (final).
#   * PPM     (0x16) : salt 3200 PPM -> then 3000 PPM (final), status On.
#
# Checksums are the low byte of the sum over [DLE .. last payload byte],
# identical to what MessageBuilder::CreateValidChecksummedMessage produces, so
# these frames pass the real Jandy generator's checksum validation unmodified.
# The interleaved W line is the app's own past output and MUST be skipped on
# replay (kept here to assert the replayer/LoadFixture ignore W-direction bytes).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
